---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Fabio Capela">
	<section class="article-grid py-24">
		<div class="main-column">
			<h1 class="text-5xl font-sans font-extrabold tracking-tighter mb-12">
				The observer <br/>
                is the observed.
			</h1>
			
			<p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
				I am Fabio Capela, a theoretical physicist interested in the intersection of differential geometry, 
                information theory, and large language models.
			</p>

            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
                My work focuses on interpreting neural networks not as black-box function approximators, 
                but as geometric objects whose training dynamics can be analyzed using the tools of modern physics.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl mt-16 mb-6">Scientific Background</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
                With a PhD in Theoretical Physics, I've spent over a decade applying mathematical rigor to 
                complex systems. You can find my previous research contributions on 
                <a href="https://arxiv.org/search/?searchtype=author&query=Capela%2C+F" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">arXiv</a>.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-[2.5rem] border border-slate-100 my-16">
                <h3 class="font-sans font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-4">Contact</h3>
                <p class="font-mono text-sm mb-0">
                    research [at] labfab.io
                </p>
            </div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
